		      		        <div id="project_question_57" class="column span-15 append-4 toppend-half bottomend-half border_t_g first last comment j_project_question" data-question-id="57">
	<div class="column first">
          <img class="avatar_large" src="https://graph.facebook.com/100000072272266/picture?type=square"/>
    	</div>
	<div class="column span-13 last">
      <h4><a href="http://collabfinder.com/person/john.novatnack">John Novatnack</a></h4>
    <h4 class="plain">I think this is an interesting idea, but I wonder if a mobile app is the best way to acquire the data.  Personally I&#039;d prefer to run this from a stationary computer that has a microphone attached to my outside window.  Much safer for the device and you&#039;ll also probably make it more likely to get data from users all day long.<br/>
<br/>
Have you considered building this is a HTML5 web app or possibly chrome extension?</h4>
    <h5 class="light_text plain timestamp">1 week ago</h5>
			</div>
	</div>
 
<div id="project_question_answers_57">
      <div id="project_question_answer_27" class="column span-15 prepend-2 append-2 toppend-half bottomend-half border_t_g first last comment j_project_answer" data-answer-id="27" data-question-id="57">
	<div class="column first">
    <img class="avatar_large" src="https://graph.facebook.com/103757/picture?type=square"/>
	</div>
	<div class="column span-13 last">
  <h4>
    <a href="http://collabfinder.com/person/jeffnovich">Jeff Novich</a>
     
      &nbsp;<span class="small red">PROJECT CREATOR</span>
      </h4>
    <h4 class="plain">Hey John - Really good suggestion. My thinking around this was to have a very low-cost, small-footprint way to monitor sound.  It could certainly be a web or desktop app, but then you&#039;ll need a laptop + a microphone which is pretty cumbersome.  If this were an iOS app, I would personally get a few used (older model) iphones and ping my network for ideal locations. I&#039;d go plug the iphone in, connect it to their wifi and let it sit somewhere for a day or a week, pick it back up and move it to a new location.  It isn&#039;t particularly hard to ask a friend to &quot;rent&quot; a plug, wifi and a spot on their fire escape. It is pretty cumbersome to ask that they run a desktop app with a mic and not mess with it for a period of time.<br/>
<br/>
The goal is to develop a proof of concept that this process could be deployed cheaply (an app + a few old iphones near wifi and power) and could generate a lot of valuable data.  I think a mobile device is ideally suited for that goal.<br/>
<br/>
Another point that I don&#039;t think I articulated very well is that this would be a process owned and run by an agency -such as the TLC or DoT.  I don&#039;t see this working effectively as a purely &quot;crowd sourced&quot; service (though maybe at some point).  So you&#039;re probably thinking about how to get an average user to take their own iPhone and stick it out the window for a day in the name of noise data.  I agree that&#039;s a hard bargain and I don&#039;t think many people will do that, which is why I&#039;d kick it off by personally placing the devices myself to learn more.<br/>
<br/>
Does that make sense?   What do you think?</h4>
    <h5 class="light_text plain timestamp">6 days ago</h5>
			</div>
</div>
  </div>
